      "content": "The current Supreme Court's interpretation of the Second Amendment is a heavily debated topic, with strong arguments on both sides. Proponents of their current rulings argue they are faithfully applying the text and history of the amendment, emphasizing an individual right to bear arms. Critics, however, contend that their modern interpretations represent judicial overreach, stretching the founders' original intent beyond what the text supported. Ultimately, the legal argument hinges on whether one prioritizes originalism or evolving interpretations of constitutional rights.",
