      "content": "thanks that's helpful. so if you're saying originalism is the more \"demonstrably consistent\" and \"rigorous\" way to do it, then isn't the \"living constitution\" approach basically just a way for judges to push their own political agendas under the guise of law? it feels like if you don't follow the original text, you're just practicing politics instead of actual law.",
